    "Figure 14:14Figure 14: Same visualization setup as in figure6, but using hard classifications to explicitly distinguish between prediction outcomes.",
    "Voxels are colored according to their classification result: true positives (black), true negatives (white), false positives (amber), and false negatives (teal).",
    "This representation highlights the spatial distribution of correct and incorrect predictions across the segmented region.",
    "Table 1:1Halo mass binning schemes used to construct the three datasets.",
    "Bin edges are given in units of log 10DatasetHalo mass bin123456110.4 -11.4 11.4 -12.4 12.4 -13.4>13.4--210.4 -11.2 11.2 -12.0 12.0 -12.8 12.8 -13.4>13.4-310.4 -11.0 11.0 -11.6 11.6 -12.2 12.2 -12.8 12.8 -13.4 >13.4 Table 3:3Optimal classification thresholds per output class, selected according to three different criteria: maximum F1 score (equivalent to the maximum Dice coefficient for hard classifications), minimum Euclidean distance to the ideal point (0, 1) on the ROC curve, and maximum Youden's J statistic."
